                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6311/220</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Austria-Hungary</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PFC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Penfield</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-27T15:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1916, 3 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 28, 11 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1464. While transacting routine business yesterday afternoon with the Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs, reference was made to the recent attack on him in the
                    Hungarian Parliament for having no Ambassador in Washington. Started wholly
                    informal, ended in the definite inquiry if you could arrange for a safe-conduct;
                    if so, Minister for Foreign Affairs would early ask <hi rend="italic"
                        >agrément</hi> for high-class representative. Obviously this Government want
                    no publicity until assured that your request for a safe-conduct will be granted
                    by the Entente. This I promised. Kindly cable me early. Beg call attention your
                    telegram No. 1226 of May 16 last.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Penfield</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
